Grammars are invented in Perl6 just for that. Perl5 has module[0] for that implemented using recursive regex&#x27;s.<p>Example of LaTeX parser:<p><pre><code>    use Regexp::Grammars;
    $parser = qr{
        <File>
        <rule: File>       <[Element]>*
        <rule: Element>    <Command> | <Literal>
        <rule: Command>    \  <Literal> <Options>? <Args>?
        <rule: Options>    \[  <[Option]>+ % (,)  \]
        <rule: Args>       \{  <[Element]>*  \}
        <rule: Option>     [^][\$&%#_{}~^\s,]+
        <rule: Literal>    [^][\$&%#_{}~^\s]+
    }xms
</code></pre>
